Download Page for libgimp2.0_2.8.22+git32525-f54659d-1_i386.deb

If you are running Debian, it is strongly suggested to use a package manager like aptitude or synaptic to download and install packages, instead of doing so manually via this website.

1. Open a terminal and install apt-transport-https

sudo apt-get install apt-transport-https

2. Add this line to your /etc/apt/sources.list :

deb https://notesalexp.org/debian/sid/ sid main

3. Fetch and install the GnuPG key

sudo aptitude update && sudo aptitude install notesalexp-keyring

sudo aptitude update

or

wget -O - https://notesalexp.org/debian/alexp_key.asc | sudo apt-key add -

sudo aptitude update

4. Enjoy

sudo aptitude install libgimp2.0

You can download the requested file from the pool/main/g/gimp subdirectory at this link:

http://notesalexp.org/sid/main/g/gimp/libgimp2.0_2.8.22+git32525-f54659d-1_i386.deb
